#
# $Id$
# Build file for EQ 1.5 production version
# Format:
# <input_file> <output_file> <flag>
#
# Input file - absolute path to a file that will be included into EQ build.
#     %ORIGIN% keyword can be used to specify source EQ directory.
#
# Output file - relative path to output file. This path is always relative to
#     EQ build directory. If output filename is omitted (only subdirectory
#     is specified) then the Build.pl will use the same name of file as is
#     in <input_file>. In this case subdirectory name should always end with '/'.
#
# Flag - The following flags are supported:
#
#     SETX - 'x' (executable) mode will be set for output file. This option
#         works only on UNIX.
#
#     SMALL - if this option is specified together with TOEXE option then
#         a perl script is compiled with "-small" perl2exe option instead
#         of default "-tiny" option.
#
#     FREE - if this option is specified together with TOEXE option then
#         a perl script is compiled with "--freestanding" perlapp option instead
#         of default "--dependent" option.
#
#     TOEXE - all references to perl scripts inside of output file will be
#         replaced with references to similar executable file (i. e.
#         reference to '/usr/bin/perl MyScript.pl' will be replaced with
#         'MyScript.exe'. If input file is a perl script then it will also
#         be compiled.
#
#     UNIX - current file is included in the EQ build only if builting a
#         Unix version.
#
#     WIN - current file is included in the EQ build only if builting a
#         Windows version.
#

